topic.title: Firmware Log Retrieval Command

body.p: All the tables in this topic are revised as per the discussion with Danny Moore. Please provide your feedback. Note that the older tables are hidden with MSCC Internal tag. Also, please do not delete the old tables till the review is complete.MRPC Command ID: 0x06

MRPC Firmware Log Retrieval command (referred to as Firmware Log Retrieval command in this document) is used to retrieve the log data and the fatal error debug information from the firmware. It contains the following sub commands to retrieve log and fatal error debug information.There are eight commands given -- should we replace seven to eight in the line above? Replace it with 'the following' I have replaced the sub-commands in the table below. Also not that "seven" in the sentence above is replaced with "eight".

table.title: MRPC Firmware Log Retrieval Sub-Commands

entry.p: Retrieve APP log entries from RAM.
Retrieve APP log entries from Flash.
Is this error handling or handing? Just to make sure we are correct. "error handling" is correct done.Retrieve Memlog information from Flash in last fatal error handling dump.
Retrieve Generic Registers context from Flash in last fatal error handling dump.
Retrieve system stack information from Flash in last fatal error handling dump.
Retrieve thread stack information from Flash in last fatal error handling dump.
Retrieve all threads information from Flash in last fatal error handling dump.
Invalidate the log information in the NVLOG partition.
Set/Get the log severity of a specific Module ID.

body.p: The APP log can be retrieved from RAM or Flash, and can be retrieved from a specified entry index. If the firmware log buffer size is larger than the log retrieval window, multiple log retrieval commands can be issued to retrieve all the log entries.

section.title: Example for Firmware Log Retrieval Sub-Commands (0-1):
section.p: The sequence below can be used to retrieve all firmware log from the beginning of RAM:

li.p: Write address 0 with data: 0x00000000 0x00000000 0x00000000 0x00000000 0xFFFFFFFF
Write address 2048 with data: 6
Read return data from address 1024
If Next Start Entry is 0x1F and Log Count Remaining is non-zero, continue reading the log.
Write address 2048 with data: 6
Read return data from address 1024
Continue to send the command until the Log Count Remaining is 0 in the returned data.

body.p: The following example steps show how to use SubCmd 2 to retrieve memlog information.

li.p: Fill the MRPC input parameters: SubCmd 2 , INFO_OFFSET 0, RETRIEVE_LEN_REQ:0x10.
Issue the MRPC SubCmd.
Check the status and the return value of this SubCmd.

p.cmdname: Read address 0x808 for 1 DW, if return Value is 0, it means success; otherwise it means failure.

li.p: Read the output header.

p.cmdname: Read address 0x400 for 3 DWs, which tells the length retrieved and the remaining length of this info type.

li.p: Read the output data.

p.cmdname: Read address 0x40C for RETRIEVED_LEN bytes to get the retrieved data of this info type.

li.p: Update the input parameters (INFO_OFFSET and RETRIEVE_LEN_REQ), and then issue the SubCmd again to retrieve data continuously.
